# CLAUDE.md

This file provides guidance to Claude Code (claude.ai/code) when working with code in this repository.

## Development Commands

```bash
pnpm dev          # Start development server (Astro)
pnpm build        # Build for production (static site)
pnpm preview      # Preview production build locally
pnpm lint         # Run ESLint
```

## Project Architecture

This is an **Astro** personal portfolio/blog with a **macOS Terminal** design theme, using 100% static site generation (SSG).

### Content System

Blog posts are stored as Markdown files in `src/content/post/` with frontmatter:

```yaml
---
title: "Post Title"
subtitle: "Brief description"
date: "YYYY-MM-DD"
tags: ["tag1", "tag2"]
---
```

Posts are automatically discovered by Astro's Content Collections and rendered using:
- Built-in Markdown/MDX support
- Dynamic routes at `/blog/post/[slug]/`
- Static site generation at build time

### Key Directories

- `src/pages/` - Astro pages and routes
  - `index.astro` - Home page
  - `about.astro` - About page
  - `contact.astro` - Contact page
  - `blog/index.astro` - Blog listing
  - `blog/post/[slug].astro` - Individual blog posts
  - `robots.txt.ts` - Robots.txt endpoint
- `src/layouts/` - Layout components (BaseLayout with macOS Terminal design)
- `src/components/` - Reusable UI components (Header, Footer, PostCard)
- `src/content/post/` - Markdown blog posts (auto-discovered by Astro)
- `src/styles/` - Global CSS (Tailwind + custom terminal styles)
- `public/` - Static assets (images, etc.)

### Styling

Uses **Tailwind CSS** with custom macOS Terminal-inspired design:

- **Terminal colors**: `#1e1e1e` (bg), `#e0e0e0` (fg), `#808080` (dim), `#4a9eff` (accent)
- **Terminal window component**: Window with 3 buttons (red/yellow/green), title bar
- **Typography plugin**: `prose` class for blog content with dark theme
- **Google Fonts**: Montserrat (headings), Open Sans (body), JetBrains Mono (code/terminal)

### Fonts

- **Montserrat** - Headings and display text
- **Open Sans** - Body text
- **JetBrains Mono** - Code blocks and terminal UI

### Design Theme (macOS Terminal)

All pages use a "macOS Terminal" window design:
- Dark background (`#1e1e1e`)
- Terminal window with header and 3 control buttons
- Monospace font for UI elements
- Generous spacing and excellent readability
- Hover states on links and cards

### Code Quality

- TypeScript strict mode enabled
- ESLint with Prettier and Tailwind plugins
- Prettier with Tailwind plugin for consistent formatting

### Deployment

- **Platform**: Vercel
- **Build output**: Static site (`output: 'static'`)
- **Adapter**: `@astrojs/vercel`
- **Sitemap**: Auto-generated by `@astrojs/sitemap`

### Content Collections

Blog posts use Astro's Content Collections. Collections are auto-generated from `src/content/post/` directory. To add a new post:

1. Create a new `.md` or `.mdx` file in `src/content/post/`
2. Add frontmatter with `title`, `subtitle`, `date`, `tags`
3. The post will be automatically available at `/blog/post/[slug]/`
